article.description: Nijal Pearson had 19 points to lead five Texas State players in double figures as the Bobcats routed Texas Lutheran 103-45 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Pearson, Terry lead Texas St. over Texas Lutheran 103-45
article.linkText: Pearson, Terry lead Texas St. over Texas Lutheran 103-45
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- Nijal Pearson had 19 points to lead five Texas State players in double figures as the Bobcats routed Texas Lutheran 103-45 on Tuesday night. Eric Terry added 18 points for the Bobcats. Alonzo Sule chipped in 12, Drew Tennial scored 11 and Mason Harrell had 11. Terry also had nine rebounds for the Bobcats. Pearson had 18 points and Terry 12 in the first half as the Bobcats took a 57-18 lead into the break. Sebastian Andrade had 14 points for the Bulldogs. Texas State plays Air Force on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
